    <example>
      <summary>Get the GMP schema</summary>
      <request>
        <help format="XML"></help>
      </request>
      <response>
        <help_response status="200" status_text="OK">
          <schema format="XML" extension="xml" content_type="text/xml">
            <protocol>
              <name>Greenbone Management Protocol</name>
              <abbreviation>GMP</abbreviation>
              <summary>The management protocol of the Greenbone Vulnerability Manager</summary>
              <version>@GMP_VERSION@</version>
              <truncated>...</truncated>
              <type>
                <name>base64</name>
                <summary>Base64 encoded data</summary>
                <pattern>xsd:base64Binary</pattern>
              </type>
              <truncated>...</truncated>
              <command>
                <name>authenticate</name>
                <summary>Authenticate with the manager</summary>
                <truncated>...</truncated>
              </command>
              <truncated>...</truncated>
            </protocol>
          </schema>
        </help_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_asset</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing asset</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the modify_asset command to change an existing asset.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>asset_id</name>
        <summary>ID of asset to modify</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <o><e>comment</e></o>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>comment</name>
      <summary>Comment on asset</summary>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the comment of an asset</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_asset asset_id='914b59f8-25f5-4c8f-832c-2379cd625236'>
          <comment>New comment</comment>
        </modify_asset>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_asset_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_asset_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_config</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing config</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        This command can perform four types of actions: 1) modifying
        preferences, 2) changing the family selection, 3) changing the
        NVT selection of families, or 4) modifying basic fields like
        the name or comment.
      </p>

      <p>
        Since version 21.04 it is possible to perform multiple of these actions
        at once in the order they appear in the command. Note that the changes
        can influence each other, so this can change the overall result.
      </p>

      <p>
        The first type modifies the preferences on the config.
        If a preference includes an NVT, then the preference is an NVT preference,
        otherwise the preference is a scanner preference.  If the preference includes
        a value then the manager updates the value of the preference, otherwise the
        manager removes the preference.  The value must be base64 encoded.
      </p>

      <p>
        The second type, with a family selection, lets the client modify the
        NVTs selected by the config at a family level.  The idea is that the
        client modifies the entire family selection at once, so a client will
        often need to include many families in a family selection.
      </p>

      <p>
        The family_selection may include a growing element to indicate whether new
        families should be added to the selection.  It may also include any number
        of family elements.
      </p>

      <p>
        A family element must always include a name and may include a growing element
        and an all element.  The all element indicates whether all NVTs in the family
        should be selected.  The growing element indicates whether new NVTs in the
        family should be added to the selection as they arrive.  Leaving a family
        out of the family_selection is equivalent to including the family with all
        0 and growing 0.
      </p>

      <p>
        The effect of the all 0 and growing 0 case is subtle: if
        all NVTs were selected then all are removed (effectively removing the
        family from the config).  However if some NVTs were selected then they
        remain selected.  As a result the client must include in the
        family_selection all families that must have all NVTs selected.
      </p>

      <p>
        The third option, NVT selections, must include a family and may include any
        number of NVTs.  The manager updates each given family in the config to
        include only the given NVTs. If the family selection is also changed,
        this should be done first as it can also change the NVT selection of
        families.
      </p>

      <p>
        If there was no error with the command sent by the client, the manager will
        apply the changes to the config and will reply with a response code indicating
        success.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>config_id</name>
        <summary>ID of config to modify</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <o>><e>name</e></o>
      <o><e>comment</e></o>
      <any><e>preference</e></any>
      <o><e>family_selection</e></o>
      <any><e>nvt_selection</e></any>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>name</name>
      <summary>New name for the config</summary>
      <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>comment</name>
      <summary>New comment for the config</summary>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>preference</name>
      <pattern>
        <e>name</e>
        <o><e>nvt</e></o>
        <o><e>value</e></o>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>name</name>
        <summary>The name of the preference to modify</summary>
        <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>nvt</name>
        <summary>NVT associated with preference to modify</summary>
        <description>
          If this element is present then the preference is an NVT
          preference, otherwise it is a Scanner preference.
        </description>
        <pattern>
          <attrib>
            <name>oid</name>
            <type>oid</type>
            <required>1</required>
          </attrib>
        </pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>value</name>
        <summary>New value for preference</summary>
        <pattern><t>base64</t></pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>family_selection</name>
      <pattern>
        <o><e>growing</e></o>
        <any><e>family</e></any>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>growing</name>
        <summary>Whether new families should be added to the config</summary>
        <pattern><t>boolean_atoi</t></pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>family</name>
        <pattern>
          <o><e>all</e></o>
          <o><e>growing</e></o>
          <e>name</e>
        </pattern>
        <ele>
          <name>all</name>
          <summary>Whether to select all NVTs initially</summary>
          <pattern><t>boolean_atoi</t></pattern>
        </ele>
        <ele>
          <name>growing</name>
          <summary>Whether to add newly arrived nvts to the selection</summary>
          <pattern><t>boolean_atoi</t></pattern>
        </ele>
        <ele>
          <name>name</name>
          <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
        </ele>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>nvt_selection</name>
      <pattern>
        <e>family</e>
        <any><e>nvt</e></any>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>family</name>
        <summary>Name of family to modify</summary>
        <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>nvt</name>
        <pattern>
          <attrib>
            <name>oid</name>
            <type>oid</type>
            <required>1</required>
          </attrib>
        </pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify a config NVT preference</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_config config_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <preference>
            <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.14259"></nvt>
            <name>1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.14259:1:checkbox:UDP port scan</name>
            <value>eWVz</value>
          </preference>
        </modify_config>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_config_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_config_response>
      </response>
    </example>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify a config Scanner preference</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_config config_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <preference>
            <name>scanner:scanner:scanner:vhosts</name>
            <value>ZXhhbXBsZQ==</value>
          </preference>
        </modify_config>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_config_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_config_response>
      </response>
    </example>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the families that a config selects</summary>
      <description>
        <p>
          The outer "growing" element sets the config to add any new families
          that arrive.
        </p>
        <p>
          The client requests the Manager to keep a single selected
          family (Debian Local Security Checks), to select all NVTs in
          this family, and to automatically add any new NVTs in this family
          to the config.
        </p>
      </description>
      <request>
        <modify_config config_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <family_selection>
            <growing>1</growing>
            <family>
              <name>Debian Local Security Checks</name>
              <all>1</all>
              <growing>1</growing>
            </family>
          </family_selection>
        </modify_config>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_config_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_config_response>
      </response>
    </example>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the NVTs that a config selects in a particular family</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_config config_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <nvt_selection>
            <family>Debian Local Security Checks</family>
            <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.53797"></nvt>
            <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.63272"></nvt>
            <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.55615"></nvt>
            <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.53546"></nvt>
          </nvt_selection>
        </modify_config>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_config_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_config_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_credential</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing credential</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the modify_credential command to change an
        existing credential.
      </p>
      <p>
        The login and password can only be changed for password credentials.
        Modification of login or password on package credentials is forbidden.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>credential_id</name>
        <summary>ID of credential to modify</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <o><e>comment</e></o>
      <o><e>name</e></o>
      <o><e>allow_insecure</e></o>
      <o><e>certificate</e></o>
      <o><e>kdc</e></o>
      <o><e>kdcs</e></o>
      <o><e>key</e></o>
      <o><e>login</e></o>
      <o><e>password</e></o>
      <o><e>community</e></o>
      <o><e>auth_algorithm</e></o>
      <o><e>privacy</e></o>
      <o><e>realm</e></o>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>name</name>
      <summary>A name for the credential</summary>
      <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>comment</name>
      <summary>A comment on the credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>allow_insecure</name>
      <summary>Whether to allow insecure use of the credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        <t>boolean</t>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>certificate</name>
      <summary>The certificate for the credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>kdc</name>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
      <summary>Deprecated: This element is deprecated. Use kdcs instead. The Kerberos KDC (key distribution center(s))</summary>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>kdcs</name>
      <summary>Multiple Kerberos KDCs</summary>
      <description>
        <p>List of one or more Kerberos Key Distribution Centers (KDCs).</p>
      </description>
      <pattern>
        <any><e>kdc</e></any>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>kdc</name>
        <summary>A single Kerberos Key Distribution Center</summary>
        <pattern>text</pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>key</name>
      <pattern>
        <o><e>phrase</e></o>
        <or>
          <e>private</e>
          <e>public</e>
        </or>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>phrase</name>
        <summary>Key passphrase</summary>
        <pattern>
          text
        </pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>private</name>
        <summary>Private key</summary>
        <pattern>
          text
        </pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>public</name>
        <summary>Public key</summary>
        <pattern>
          text
        </pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>login</name>
      <summary>The user name of the credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>password</name>
      <summary>The password for the credential login</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>community</name>
      <summary>The SNMP community</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>auth_algorithm</name>
      <summary>Authentication algorithm for SNMP, either md5 or sha1</summary>
      <pattern>
        <alts>
          <alt>md5</alt>
          <alt>sha1</alt>
        </alts>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>privacy</name>
      <pattern>
        <e>algorithm</e>
        <e>password</e>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>algorithm</name>
        <summary>The SNMP privacy algorithm, either aes or des</summary>
        <pattern>
          <alts>
            <alt>aes</alt>
            <alt>des</alt>
          </alts>
        </pattern>
      </ele>
      <ele>
        <name>password</name>
        <summary>The SNMP privacy password</summary>
        <pattern>
          text
        </pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>realm</name>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
      <summary>The Kerberos realm</summary>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the comment of an credential</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_credential credential_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <comment>Credential for all machines in lab 4.</comment>
        </modify_credential>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_credential_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_credential_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_setting</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing setting</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the modify_setting command to change an existing
        setting.  These are user settings that can be controlled via GMP.
        The settings "Password" and "Timezone" can be modified by name, the
        rest by UUID.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>setting_id</name>
        <type>uuid</type>
      </attrib>
      <e>name</e>
      <e>value</e>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>name</name>
      <summary>The name of the setting</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>value</name>
      <summary>The value of the setting, in base64 encoding</summary>
      <pattern><t>base64</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the timezone</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_setting>
          <name>Timezone</name>
          <value>QWZyaWNhL0pvaGFubmVzYnVyZw==</value>
        </modify_setting>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_setting_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_setting_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_target</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing target</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the modify_target command to change an existing target.
      </p>
      <p>
        If the SSH elevate credential is set, the SSH credential must also be
        set. The SSH elevate credential and the SSH credential must differ.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>target_id</name>
        <summary>ID of target to modify</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <o><e>comment</e></o>
      <o><e>name</e></o>
      <o><e>hosts</e></o>
      <o><e>exclude_hosts</e></o>
      <o><e>ssh_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>ssh_elevate_credential</e></o>
      <o>
        <or>
          <e>krb5_credential</e>
          <e>smb_credential</e>
        </or>
      </o>
      <o><e>esxi_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>snmp_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>ssh_lsc_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>smb_lsc_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>esxi_lsc_credential</e></o>
      <o><e>port_list</e></o>
      <o><e>alive_tests</e></o>
      <o><e>reverse_lookup_only</e></o>
      <o><e>reverse_lookup_unify</e></o>
      <o><e>allow_simultaneous_ips</e></o>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>comment</name>
      <summary>Comment on target</summary>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>name</name>
      <summary>Name of target</summary>
      <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>hosts</name>
      <summary>Comma-separated list of target hosts</summary>
      <pattern>text</pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>exclude_hosts</name>
      <summary>Comma-separated list of hosts to exclude</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>ssh_credential</name>
      <summary>SSH credential to use on target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>ssh_elevate_credential</name>
      <summary>SSH elevate credential to use on target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>smb_credential</name>
      <summary>SMB credential to use on target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>krb5_credential</name>
      <summary>Kerberos 5 login credentials for target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>esxi_credential</name>
      <summary>ESXi credential to use on target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>snmp_credential</name>
      <summary>SNMP credential to use on target</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>ssh_lsc_credential</name>
      <summary>Deprecated: use ssh_credential. SSH credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>smb_lsc_credential</name>
      <summary>Deprecated: use ssh_credential. SMB credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>esxi_lsc_credential</name>
      <summary>Deprecated: use esxi_credential. ESXi credential</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>port_list</name>
      <summary>Port List describing ports to scan</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>alive_tests</name>
      <summary>Which alive tests to use</summary>
      <description>
        Instead of the sub-elements a string representation of the
        old predefined alive test selections can be used, but this is
        deprecated.
      </description>
      <pattern>
        <any><e>alive_test</e></any>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>alive_test</name>
        <summary>
          A single alive test to use.
          "Scan Config Default" and "Consider Alive" can only be used alone
        </summary>
        <pattern>
          <t>alive_test</t>
        </pattern>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>reverse_lookup_only</name>
      <summary>Whether to scan only hosts that have names</summary>
      <pattern><t>boolean</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>reverse_lookup_unify</name>
      <summary>
        Whether to scan only one IP when multiple IPs have the same name
      </summary>
      <pattern><t>boolean</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>allow_simultaneous_ips</name>
      <summary>
        Whether to scan multiple IPs of the same host simultaneously
      </summary>
      <pattern><t>boolean</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify the name of a target</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_target target_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <name>Upstairs Lab</name>
        </modify_target>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_target_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_target_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>modify_task</name>
    <summary>Modify an existing task</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the modify_task command to change an existing
        task.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>task_id</name>
        <summary>ID of task to modify</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <or>
        <e>comment</e>
        <!-- Actually at least one, else command is empty. -->
        <any><e>alert</e></any>
        <e>config</e>
        <e>name</e>
        <e>preferences</e>
        <e>schedule</e>
        <e>schedule_periods</e>
        <e>scanner</e>
        <e>target</e>
<e>file</e>
      </or>
    </pattern>
    <ele>
      <name>comment</name>
      <summary>The comment on the task</summary>
      <pattern>
        text
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>alert</name>
      <summary>Task alert</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>config</name>
      <summary>The scan configuration used by the task</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>name</name>
      <summary>The name of the task</summary>
      <pattern><t>name</t></pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>preferences</name>
      <pattern>
        <any><e>preference</e></any>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>preference</name>
        <pattern>
          <e>scanner_name</e>
          <e>value</e>
        </pattern>
        <ele>
          <name>scanner_name</name>
          <summary>Compact name of preference, from scanner</summary>
          <pattern>text</pattern>
        </ele>
        <ele>
          <name>value</name>
          <pattern>text</pattern>
        </ele>
      </ele>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>schedule</name>
      <summary>Task schedule</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>schedule_periods</name>
      <summary>
        A limit to the number of times the task will be scheduled, or 0 for no limit
      </summary>
      <pattern>
        <t>integer</t>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>scanner</name>
      <summary>Task scanner</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <ele>
      <name>target</name>
      <summary>The hosts scanned by the task</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>id</name>
          <type>uuid</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
<ele>
      <name>file</name>
      <summary>File to attach to task</summary>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>name</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <t>base64</t>
        <attrib>
          <name>action</name>
          <type>
            <alts>
              <alt>update</alt>
              <alt>remove</alt>
            </alts>
          </type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </ele>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Modify a task comment</summary>
      <request>
        <modify_task task_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6">
          <comment>Monthly scan of the webserver.</comment>
        </modify_task>
      </request>
      <response>
        <modify_task_response status="200" status_text="OK">
        </modify_task_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>move_task</name>
    <summary>
      Moves an existing task to another slave scanner or the master
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        If a scan is running, this command will stop the task and resume it
        after reassigning to the new scanner or master.
        Note that in this case, the command will wait until the task has been
        requested to resume.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>task_id</name>
        <summary>ID of task to reassign</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
      <attrib>
        <name>slave_id</name>
        <summary>ID of slave to reassign to, empty for master</summary>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
    </pattern>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Move a task to a slave</summary>
      <request>
        <move_task task_id="254cd3ef-bbe1-4d58-859d-21b8d0c046c6"
                   slave_id="97390ade-e075-11df-9973-002264764cea">
        </move_task>
      </request>
      <response>
        <move_task_response status="200" status_text="OK"/>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>start_task</name>
    <summary>Manually start an existing task</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the start_task command to manually start an
        existing task.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>task_id</name>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
    </pattern>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <e>report_id</e>
      </pattern>
      <ele>
        <name>report_id</name>
        <summary>The id of the report</summary>
        <pattern>
          <t>uuid</t>
        </pattern>
      </ele>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Start a task</summary>
      <request>
        <start_task task_id="267a3405-e84a-47da-97b2-5fa0d2e8995e">
        </start_task>
      </request>
      <response>
        <start_task_response status="200" status_text="OK">
          <report_id>330ee785-c2c0-4d4c-ab96-725142c9b789</report_id>
        </start_task_response>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>stop_task</name>
    <summary>Stop a running task</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the stop_task command to manually stop a
        running task.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
      <attrib>
        <name>task_id</name>
        <type>uuid</type>
        <required>1</required>
      </attrib>
    </pattern>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Stop a running task</summary>
      <request>
        <stop_task task_id="267a3405-e84a-47da-97b2-5fa0d2e8995e">
        </stop_task>
      </request>
      <response>
        <stop_task_response status="200" status_text="OK"/>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <command>
    <name>sync_config</name>
    <summary>Synchronize a config with a scanner</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The client uses the "sync_config" command to request an OSP
        config synchronization with a scanner, adding new parameters and
        removing old ones.
      </p>
    </description>
    <pattern>
    </pattern>
    <response>
      <pattern>
        <attrib>
          <name>status</name>
          <type>status</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
        <attrib>
          <name>status_text</name>
          <type>text</type>
          <required>1</required>
        </attrib>
      </pattern>
    </response>
    <example>
      <summary>Sync the config</summary>
      <request>
        <sync_config>
        </sync_config>
      </request>
      <response>
        <sync_config_response status="202" status_text="OK, request submitted"/>
      </response>
    </example>
  </command>
  <!-- Compatibility changes between versions. -->
  <change>
    <command>GET_RESULTS</command>
    <summary>New element &quot;compliance&quot; in &quot;get_results&quot; response</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        New element &quot;compliance&quot; is added to specify the compliance state
        for a result.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.6</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_FEEDS</command>
    <summary>Extend &quot;get_feeds&quot; command</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        &quot;get_feeds&quot; command is extended with &quot;feed_owner_set&quot;
        and &quot;feed_resources_access&quot;.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.6</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>Changes for &quot;CVE&quot; and &quot;CPE&quot; info elements</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        For CVE info elements, &quot;configuration_nodes&quot; and &quot;references&quot;
        are added.
      </p>
      <p>
        For CPE info elements, &quot;nvd_id&quot; is replaced by &quot;cpe_name_id&quot;
        and &quot;status&quot; is replaced by &quot;deprecated&quot;.
        &quot;references&quot; and &quot;deprecated_by&quot; are added.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.6</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_RESOURCE_NAMES</command>
    <summary>The new command GET_RESOURCE_NAMES has been added</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        A new command to get one or many names and IDs for items of given type.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.5</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_TASK, CREATE_USER, GET_TASKS, GET_USERS, MODIFY_TASK, MODIFY_USER</command>
    <summary>Removed network interface (iface) options</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The option to choose the source interface in the form of the task
        preference &quot;source_iface&quot; has been removed as well as
        the &quot;ifaces&quot; element of users to limit the allowed network
        interfaces.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>Removed the Secinfo-type OVALDEF from the GET_INFO command
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The type OVALDEF is removed from the list of possible types for
        the GET_INFO command.
      </p>
      <p>
        OVAL Definitions are no longer supported.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>22.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>Replaced CVSS score elements by integer score</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The elements CVSS and MAX_CVSS of CPEs, CVEs, OVAL definitions and
        CERT advisories are replaced by the SEVERITY element.
      </p>
      <p>
        NVTs still contain the CVSS_BASE element for backward compatibility
        of reports. However, the use of the CVSS_BASE element is deprecated
        and the score attribute of the new SEVERITIES element should be used
        instead.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>Replaced CVSS vector components of CVEs with vector string</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The elements VECTOR, COMPLEXITY, AUTHENTICATION,
        CONFIDENTIALITY_IMPACT, INTEGRITY_IMPACT and AVAILABILITY_IMPACT
        are replaced by the CVSS_VECTOR element that contains the CVSS base
        vector in a shorter string representation.
      </p>
      <p>
        This vector string can also use newer CVSS versions like 3.1 if
        available.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Removed element SEVERITY_CLASS from element REPORT</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element SEVERITY_CLASS contained the range specification for the applied classification scheme.
        There is only fixed scheme left, so the specificion is not needed anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS, GET_RESULTS</command>
    <summary>Remove elements AUTOFP and AUTO_TYPE from element FILTERS</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element to specify the autofp value and the related auto_type for a filter is removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_SCANNER, MODIFY_SCANNER, GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>GMP scanners have been removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The scanner type "GMP" has been removed.  This is the original "slave"
        feature, where a gvmd (the master) controls another gvmd (the slave)
        via GMP.
      </p>
      <p>
        Existing GMP scanners are automatically migrated to type "OpenVAS".
        The "OpenVAS" scanner type uses the OSP protocol, and is better suited
        to the master-slave scenario.
      </p>
      <p>
        CREATE_SCANNER and MODIFY_SCANNER no longer accept type "4".
      </p>
      <p>
        In the report XML, as returned by GET_REPORTS, SLAVE has been removed
        from REPORT/TASK.
      </p>
      <p>
        All other scanner related commands work as before, but there are no
        GMP scanners for them to work with.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Removed element RESULT_COUNT/DEBUG from element REPORT</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element DEBUG inside RESULT_COUNT is removed. Vulnerability tests do
        not produce debug messages since 2012.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>21.4</version>
  </change>

  <change>
    <command>CREATE_TARGET</command>
    <summary>Default port list removed from CREATE_TARGET</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        CREATE_TARGET will no longer automatically add a port list to the
        target if a port list or range is not given.  In other words, it
        is now mandatory to supply either PORT_LIST or PORT_RANGE.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_SCHEDULES</command>
    <summary>Classic schedule elements removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The classic schedule elements like PERIOD, DURATION and BYDAY have been
        removed.  Schedules are represented using iCalendar elements.
      </p>
      <p>
        This includes the filter keyword 'initial_offset'.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>HOST_PROGRESS has been removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element HOST_PROGRESS in PROGRESS has been removed.
      </p>
      <p>
        To be precise, it is no longer possible for the element to be included
        in reports, as it was only sent for OTP scanners, and OTP scanners were
        removed in an earlier version.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>COMMANDS</command>
    <summary>COMMANDS has been removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command COMMANDS has been removed.  It is no longer possible
        to group multiple commands into a single command.  It is, however,
        still possible to run multiple commands sequentially on the same
        GMP connection.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_AGENT, DELETE_AGENT, GET_AGENTS, MODIFY_AGENT, VERIFY_AGENT</command>
    <summary>The agents facility has been removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Agents have been removed entirely.  This includes all agents commands
        and the filter setting 'Agents Filter' (UUID
        4a1334c1-cb93-4a79-8634-103b0a50bdcd).
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_... Commands using filters</command>
    <summary>GET_... commands will default to "rows=-2" filter</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        If no filter or a filter without a rows keyword is given, the various
        GET_... commands using filters will behave as if "rows=-2" was given
        instead of "rows=-1".
      </p>
      <p>
        This means they will only return the number of rows defined by the
        "Rows Per Page" setting and the maximum amount of rows has to be
        requested explicitly with a "rows=-1" filter keyword or 
        (where available) the ignore_pagination option.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>Attribute "type" can not be "ALLINFO" anymore</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The type "ALLINFO" is not supported anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>MODIFY_REPORT</command>
    <summary>The command MODIFY_REPORT is removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command "MODIFY_REPORT" is not supported anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>20.08</version>
  </change>

  <change>
    <command>CREATE_CONFIG</command>
    <summary>NVT preferences without IDs are no longer accepted</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Importing of old scan configs that do not specify an ID for their
        NVT preferences is no longer allowed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_CONFIG</command>
    <summary>NVT preferences without IDs are no longer accepted</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Importing of old scan configs that do not specify an ID for their
        NVT preferences is no longer allowed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Default of "details" attribute is now 0</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The default of the "details" attribute has changed from 1 to 0.
        This matches the defaults of all the other GET commands.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Remove report type "assets"</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The "assets" report has been removed from GET_REPORTS.  Clients should
        instead use the GET_ASSETS command.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a result the GET_REPORTS attributes "type", "host", "pos",
        "host_first_result", "host_max_results", "host_levels" and
        "host_search_phrase" were removed.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the response side REPORT/REPORT/HOST_COUNT has been removed,
        as this was only returned by the assets reports.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_PREFERENCES, GET_CONFIGS</command>
    <summary>Add NVT Preferences ID</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The PREFERENCE element in GET_PREFERENCES and GET_CONFIGS responses
        contains an ID subelement. The ID should help in identifying
        preferences within the same nvt instead of using the preference name
        which may be changed.
      </p>
      <p>
        The content of the elements CVE_ID, BUGTRAQ_ID and XREFS is now integrated
        into the REFS element.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>9.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_NVTS, GET_INFO</command>
    <summary>New element REFS replaces CVE_ID, BUGTRAQ_ID, XREFS and CERT_REFS</summary>
    <version>9.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        The former element CERT_REFS is now named REFS and the id's for the type
        are now lower case, ie. "cert-bund" and "dfn-cert" instead of "CERT-Bund" and "DFN-CERT".
      </p>
      <p>
        The content of the elements CVE_ID, BUGTRAQ_ID and XREFS is now integrated
        into the REFS element.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS, GET_RESULTS</command>
    <summary>New element RESULT/NVT/REFS replaces RESULT/NVT/CERT</summary>
    <version>9.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        The former element CERT is now named REFS and the id's for the type
        are now lower case, ie. "cert-bund" and "dfn-cert" instead of "CERT-Bund" and "DFN-CERT".
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS, GET_RESULTS</command>
    <summary>Elements RESULT/NVT/CVE, RESULT/NVT/BID and RESULT/NVT/XREF consolidated into RESULT/NVT/REFS</summary>
    <version>9.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        The content of former elements CVE and BID are now also part of REFS and the
        respective REF types are "cve" and "bid".
      </p>
      <p>
        The content of former element XREF is now also part of REFS and the
        respective REF type is the former prefix of the XREF, for example "URL".
      </p>
      <p>
        The "NOCVE", "NOXREF" and "NOBID" strings that previously indicated the absence
        of a CVE, XREF or BID are not applied anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>

  <change>
    <command>CREATE_FILTER, CREATE_TARGET</command>
    <summary>NAME MAKE_UNIQUE removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The MAKE_UNIQUE subelement of the NAME given in the command is removed.
        The client should instead check if the creation fails because of a
        duplicate name and retry with a different one.
      </p>
      <p>
        This does, however, have no effect on the automatic naming when
        copying a resource without giving a name.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_NVTS</command>
    <summary>Remove COPYRIGHT</summary>
    <version>8.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        COPYRIGHT is removed from NVT, as it is no longer supported by the
        scanner.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>The report type &quot;prognostic&quot; has been removed.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The report type &quot;prognostic&quot; has been removed. Instead, tasks
        using the CVE Scanner should be used.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>All Commands</command>
    <summary>OMP is renamed to Greenbone Management Protocol (GMP)</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The OpenVAS Management Protocol (OMP) is renamed to Greenbone Management Protocol (GMP).
        The protocol as such does not change except for the changes documented here
        between OMP 7.0 and GMP 8.0.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_TAG, GET_TAGS, MODIFY_TAG</command>
    <summary>RESOURCE replaced with RESOURCES, removed filter keywords</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In the tag commands the single RESOURCE element is replaced with a
        RESOURCES element which contains the TYPE and which for CREATE_TAG
        and MODIFY_TAG may contain one or more RESOURCE elements to specify
        the resources the tag is to be attached to.
      </p>
      <p>
        To get the resources a tag is attached to, use a GET_... command of the
        type given in the RESOURCES / TYPE element with the tag_id keyword
        in the filter.
      </p>
      <p>
        Additionally the tag filter keywords orphan, resource,
        resource_location, resource_name and resource_uuid have been removed
        from GET_TAGS. Instead the keyword resources has been added which
        selects the total number of resources a tag is attached to.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>SYNC_FEED, SYNC_SCAP, SYNC_CERT</command>
    <summary>Commands removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The SYNC_FEED, SYNC_SCAP and SYNC_CERT commands have been removed, as
        they are no longer used by GSA, and they have been (or will be)
        superseded by automatic feed updating.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>HOST_START and HOST_END no longer returned</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element REPORT no longer contains the elements HOST_START and HOST_END.
      </p>
      <p>
        Both elements were already redundant. The elements START and END of
        the REPORT element HOST contain the same timestamps.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TASKS</command>
    <summary>REPORTS no longer returned, and RESULT_COUNT only sent with details</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element REPORTS, which contained a summary of every report on the
        task, is no longer included in the GET_TASKS response.
      </p>
      <p>
        Similarly, the element RESULT_COUNT is now only included in
        GET_TASKS_RESPONSE when the "details" attribute is true.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_NVTS</command>
    <summary>Response element CATEGORY is now an integer value instead of a string</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element CATEGORY was using a string representation of an integer enumeration.
        Now the original integer representation is used.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>The returned report element has now a element named gmp instead of omp</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element REPORT contained an element OMP to indicate the version. Now there
        is the element GMP to indicate the version.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_VULNS</command>
    <summary>The new command GET_VULNS has been added</summary>
    <description></description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_SETTINGS, GET_REPORTS, MODIFY_SETTING</command>
    <summary>Severity class OpenVAS Classic removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Severity Class "OpenVAS Classic" (short name "classic", UUID
        "dc1d556a-89e1-11e3-bc21-406186ea4fc5") has been removed.
      </p>
      <p>
        When migrating to this version all users using the "OpenVAS Classic"
        class will be switched to "NVD Vulnerability Severity Ratings".
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TASKS, GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Task status "Internal Error" renamed to "Interrupted"</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The task status "Internal Error" is now called "Interrupted", to
        better fit its function.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_INFO, GET_NVTS</command>
    <summary>VERSION element removed from NVTs</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The VERSION element has been removed from NVTs.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </change>

  <change>
    <command>GET_NVT_FEED_VERSION</command>
    <summary>Command removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The GET_NVT_FEED_VERSION command has been removed, as it has been
        superseded by the GET_FEEDS command.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TASKS, MODIFY_TASK</command>
    <summary>Element SLAVE removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Slaves have been replaced by GMP Scanners, therefore the SLAVE
        elements of commands GET_TASKS and MODIFY_TASK have been removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_CREDENTIALS</command>
    <summary>Attribute "slaves" and element SLAVES removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Slaves have been replaced by GMP Scanners, therefore the "slaves"
        attribute and CREDENTIAL/SLAVES element of GET_CREDENTIALS have been
        removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_TASK</command>
    <summary>Element SLAVE removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Slaves have been replaced by GMP Scanners, therefore the SLAVE element
        of CREATE_TASK has been removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_SLAVE, DELETE_SLAVE, GET_SLAVES, MODIFY_SLAVE</command>
    <summary>Commands removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        Slaves have been replaced by GMP Scanners, therefore the CREATE_SLAVE,
        DELETE_SLAVE, GET_SLAVES and MODIFY_SLAVE commands have been removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>DESCRIBE_FEED, DESCRIBE_SCAP, DESCRIBE_CERT</command>
    <summary>Commands replaced with GET_FEEDS</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The commands DESCRIBE_FEED, DESCRIBE_SCAP and DESCRIBE_CERT have been
        replaced with a single command, GET_FEEDS.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORT_FORMATS, CREATE_REPORT_FORMAT</command>
    <summary>Element GLOBAL removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The GLOBAL element has been removed from REPORT_FORMAT.  The element
        will simply be ignored by CREATE_REPORT_FORMAT.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>DESCRIBE_AUTH, MODIFY_AUTH</command>
    <summary>Response attributes "key" and "value" moved to elements</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The attributes "key" and "value" of AUTH_CONF_SETTING have been moved
        to new child elements of AUTH_CONF_SETTING, KEY and VALUE.  This is in order
        to preserve whitespace in the settings.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>All GET_... commands</command>
    <summary>Limit on number of returned rows introduced</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The new setting "Max Rows Per Page" introduces a hard upper limit
        on the number of rows return by any GET command, regardless of the
        value of the "rows" term in the filter.
      </p>
      <p>
        The setting defaults to 1000 and can be changed globally via the
        --max-rows option.  A value of 0 indicates no limit, which is the
        previous behaviour.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_CREDENTIALS</command>
    <summary>Credential types renamed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The TYPE element in the response will contain "up" instead of "pass"
        for username + password credentials and "usk" instead of "gen" for
        username + SSH key ones.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_LSC_CREDENTIAL, DELETE_LSC_CREDENTIAL, GET_LSC_CREDENTIALS, MODIFY_LSC_CREDENTIAL</command>
    <summary>Resource type and commands renamed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The type LSC_CREDENTIAL has been renamed to CREDENTIAL, so
        the CREATE_LSC_CREDENTIAL command is now named CREATE_CREDENTIAL,
        GET_LSC_CREDENTIALS is named GET_CREDENTIALS, etc.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_SCANNER, GET_SCANNERS, MODIFY_SCANNER</command>
    <summary>key_priv and key_pub replaced by credential</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The key_priv and key_pub elements have been replaced by a credential
        one referencing a "cc" (client certificate) type credential.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_SLAVE, GET_SLAVES, MODIFY_SLAVE</command>
    <summary>username and password replaced by credential</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The username and password elements have been replaced by a credential
        one referencing a "up" (username + password) type credential.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TARGETS</command>
    <summary>&quot;lsc_&quot; removed from credential element names</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The elements ssh_lsc_credential, smb_lsc_credential and
        esxi_lsc_credential have been renamed to ssh_credential, smb_credential
        and esxi_credential.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>7.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>PAUSE_TASK, RESUME_PAUSED_TASK</command>
    <summary>Commands removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The task pausing feature has been removed and thus, the PAUSE_TASK and
        RESUME_PAUSED_TASK commands don't exist anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>RESUME_OR_START_TASK</command>
    <summary>Command removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        As part of the consolidation of the start/resume handling of tasks,
        the command RESUME_OR_START_TASK was removed. Use START_TASK for new executions.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_TARGET, MODIFY_TARGET</command>
    <summary>Element TARGET_LOCATOR removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element TARGET_LOCATOR was removed from CREATE_TARGET and
        MODIFY_TARGET.  This was an older, unused feature.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_RESULTS</command>
    <summary>"result" elements moved to response root element</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The "result" elements returned by the GET_RESULTS command are no
        longer nested inside a "results" element but directly inside the
        "get_results_response". The "results" element is used to return the
        "max" and "start" attributes like similar elements for other types.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TARGET_LOCATORS</command>
    <summary>Command removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command GET_TARGET_LOCATORS was removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TASKS</command>
    <summary>Attribute "rcfile" and associate RCFILE removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The attribute "rcfile" and associate response element RCFILE were
        removed.  It is no longer possible to get an openvasrc configuration
        for a task.  This feature was primarily introduced to support the
        GTK frontend openvas-client, which is no longer maintained.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_CONFIG, CREATE_TASK, MODIFY_TASK</command>
    <summary>RCFILE removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The element RCFILE was removed.  It is no longer possible to create
        or modify a config or task from an openvasrc file.  This feature was
        primarily introduced to support the GTK frontend openvas-client, which
        is no longer maintained.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_LSC_CREDENTIAL</command>
    <summary>KEY/PUBLIC removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The child PUBLIC of element KEY was removed, because public keys are
        now extracted from the private key.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>6.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_FILTERS, CREATE_FILTER, MODIFY_FILTER</command>
    <summary>Filter type "report" is now "result"</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The filter type "report" has been renamed to "result".  Filters of
        this type apply to the results in a report, as used for example on
        the GSA "Report: Results" page.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name "report" is now used for a new filter type.  This filter
        type applies to lists of reports, as used for example on the GSA
        "Reports" page.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>CREATE_USER, MODIFY_USER</command>
    <summary>ROLE is identified by "id" attribute</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In OMP 4.0 these commands were served by OpenVAS Administrator.
      </p>
      <p>
        The attribute "id" is now used to specify a user's role, in the
        ROLE element.  Previously this was done using the NAME element inside
        ROLE.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_USERS</command>
    <summary>Attributes name and sort_order removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In OMP 4.0 this command was served by OpenVAS Administrator.
      </p>
      <p>
        The attributes name and sort_order have been remove from the
        GET_USERS in OpenVAS Manager.  Equivalent functionality is available
        using filters (with the filter and filt_id attributes).
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_USERS</command>
    <summary>ROLE is optional, and role name has moved into NAME</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In OMP 4.0 this command was served by OpenVAS Administrator.
      </p>
      <p>
        With the new role management, zero or more ROLEs may be present in
        USER.  The name of the role is now in ROLE/NAME instead of directly
        in the text of ROLE.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_NVTS</command>
    <summary>Fingerprint element removed</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The fingerprint element has been removed as signature keys aren't sent
        by the scanner anymore and thus, aren't stored in Manager DB anymore.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_DEPENDENCIES</command>
    <summary>
      Command removed
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command GET_DEPENDENCIES has been removed.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>MODIFY_TARGET</command>
    <summary>
      Missing elements now leave the associate target property alone
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        MODIFY_TARGET now allows the user to modify one or more of the
        Target elements in a single command, instead of requiring all
        elements to be modified at once.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a side effect of this, leaving out an element will no longer
        set the associated target value to a default, but will leave the
        associated target value untouched.  For example, if SSH_LSC_CREDENTIAL
        is omitted from the MODIFY_TARGET command, the command will no
        longer reset the SSH credential of the target, but will leave the
        target's current SSH credential intact.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>5.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>All standard GET commands</command>
    <summary>Attribute "actions" replaced with owner filtering</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The attribute "actions" in GET commands has been removed.  The only
        implemented function of this attribute was to include observed
        resources in the listings.  For example, specifying actions="g" in a
        GET_TASKS command would include tasks that other users had made
        visible to the caller.  The new way to do this is to include
        "owner=any" in the filter.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>4.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>All standard GET commands</command>
    <summary>
      Attributes "sort_field" and "sort_order" replaced by filtering
    </summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The attributes "sort_field" and "sort_order" have been removed from
        the standard GET commands.  The new way to do this is to include
        keywords like "sort=name" and "sort-reverse=name" in the filter.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>4.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_ALERTS</command>
    <summary>"Threat level" replaced with "Severity" in alert conditions</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The alert conditions "Threat level changed" and "Threat level at least"
        have been replaced with "Severity changed" and "Severity at least"
        respectively.<br/>
        The latter now expects a data entity named "severity"
        instead of "level". Both conditions now use a numeric severity value
        instead of the old threat levels like "High", "Medium" etc.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>4.0</version>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>THREAT removed from PORT in response</summary>
    <version>4.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        In the response to GET_REPORTS the element THREAT in REPORTS/PORTS/PORT
        has been replaced with the element CVSS.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_TARGETS</command>
    <summary>PORT_RANGE not always returned within TARGET</summary>
    <version>4.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        In the response to GET_TARGETS the element PORT_RANGE in TARGETS
        is only included when details attribute is set in REQUEST.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_SCANNERS</command>
    <summary>Add mandatory value for OSP parameters</summary>
    <version>4.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        The param element now contains a mandatory element that equals 0 if
        false, 1 if true.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>
  <change>
    <command>GET_NVTS</command>
    <summary>Remove summary element</summary>
    <version>4.0</version>
    <description>
      <p>
        Remove summary element as the nvt tag includes a summary already.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>

  <change>
    <command>GET_REPORTS, GET_TASKS</command>
    <summary> Include the CVSS3 rating instead of the deprecated CVSS2 rating</summary>
    <version>22.7</version>
    <description>
      <p>
          The commands GET_REPORTS and GET_TASKS as well as the element
          report and the data type levels now include the CVSS3 rating.
      </p>
    </description>
  </change>

  <!-- Changes between 1.0 and 2.0.

     report_formats
         new  CREATE_REPORT_FORMAT, DELETE_REPORT_FORMAT, GET_REPORTS_FORMATS
              VERIFY_REPORT_FORMAT, MODIFY_REPORT_FORMAT
         GET_REPORTS  req  attrib format_id instead of attrib format
                      resp  + attribs id, format_id, extension, content_type
                            entire xml report inside report entity, like others
     Add CVE and BID to RESULT.
         in GET_RESULTS resp
         in GET_NOTES,OVERRIDES resp  when attrib result is true
     slaves
         CREATE_TASK  req  + SLAVE
         new  CREATE_SLAVE, DELETE_SLAVE, GET_SLAVES
         GET_TASKS  resp  + SLAVE
         MODIFY_TASK  req  + SLAVE
     agent trust
         GET_AGENTS  resp  + TRUST and TRUST/TIME
         new  VERIFY_AGENT
     lsc credentials
         new  MODIFY_LSC_CREDENTIAL
     HELP  req  + format attrib
           resp  + SCHEMA
     report filtered result counts
        GET_REPORTS/REPORT/RESULT_COUNT  + FILTERED and FULL
     target port ranges
        CREATE_TARGET,GET_TARGETS  + PORT_RANGE
     per-protocol target credentials
        CREATE_TARGET,GET_TARGETS  + SSH,SMB_LSC_CREDENTIAL, - LSC_CREDENTIAL
     GET_TASKS  - RESULT_COUNT
  -->

  <!-- Deprecation warnings. -->

  <deprecation>
    <command>COMMANDS</command>
    <summary>The command COMMANDS will be removed.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command COMMANDS was used to send multiple commands in one request.
        This was meant to avoid multiple server-roundtrips. Since the rountrips
        are not expensive anymore, GMP clients should send each command in
        a separate request.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </deprecation>

  <deprecation>
    <command>GET_TASKS</command>
    <summary>Drop the elements FIRST_REPORT and SECOND_LAST_REPORT.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In the current version, the response of a GET_TASKS included the elements
        FIRST_REPORT and SECOND_LAST_REPORT which were both used in early versions
        of web-ui clients. Meanwhile, a GET_REPORTS call should be used to get
        whatever report is wanted, applying a suitable filter.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </deprecation>

  <deprecation>
    <command>CREATE_REPORT</command>
    <summary>Task creation will be removed.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        The command CREATE_REPORT used to offer elements TASK/NAME and TASK/COMMENT
        in order to automatically let create a new task for the imported report.
        This functionality is going to be removed. Instead use the direct command CREATE_TASK
        prior to CREATE_REPORT.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </deprecation>

  <deprecation>
    <command>GET_REPORTS</command>
    <summary>Drop the attributes TYPE, HOST, HOST_FIRST_RESULT, HOST_MAX_RESULTS, HOST_LEVELS, HOST_SEARCH_PHRASE and POS.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>
        In the current version, TYPE can be either SCAN or ASSETS and it defaults to SCAN.
        ASSETS will be removed, because GET_ASSETS should be used instead.
        If you are using TYPE with SCAN, simply remove the TYPE attribute, because the
        type is always SCAN.
      </p>
      <p>
        The other removed attributes only had a meaning in conjunction
        where TYPE was ASSETS.
      </p>
    </description>
    <version>8.0</version>
  </deprecation>

</protocol>
